Kraft Inc said in its annualreport it expects 1987 capital expenditures to be between 250mln dlrs and 300 mln dlrs.    The company said it invested 209 mln dlrs in property,plant and equipment in 1986, up from 181 mln dlrs in 1985.    Kraft also said its advertising expenditures for 1987 areexpected to match the five-year compounded 15 pct rate ofincrease recorded in 1986, when such expenditures totaled 433mln dlrs.    Kraft said research and development expenditures rose 12pct in 1986 to 66.7 mln dlrs, and a greater increase in seen in1987.    It cited a continued emphasis on new product development,advances in cheese and edible-oil technologies, furtheradaptation of tamper-evident packaging and continueddevelopment of consumer battery technologies. Reuter&#3;